openisr (0.9.1-1) experimental; urgency=low

  * new upstream release (see CHANGES):
     * Various performance improvements
     * add udev rules for loop dev and openisrctl
     * include bash completion rules
  * add group 'isrusers' for device access
  * fix bzip2 depends/build-depends

 -- Matt Toups <mtoups@cs.cmu.edu>  Tue, 12 Feb 2008 14:09:11 -0500

openisr (0.9-1) experimental; urgency=low

  * Server changes -- this client can NOT be used with the same server
    used for 0.8.4, so do not upgrade until you are prepared to switch
    servers.
  * Vulpes replaced by Parcelkeeper
  * Parcel format changes: AES encryption, SQLite keyring, UUID
  * New hoard cache implementation
     * hoard cache is shared across parcels, data downloaded only once
     * new hoard cache management commands: lshoard, rmhoard, checkhoard
  * ~/.openisr.conf is now ~/.openisrrc
  * Many more changes and bugfixes, see CHANGES
  
 -- Matt Toups <mtoups@cs.cmu.edu>  Thu, 13 Dec 2007 13:51:33 -0500

openisr (0.8.4-2) experimental; urgency=low

  * To make upgrades smoother, only Replace: openisr-modules-source

 -- Matt Toups <mtoups@cs.cmu.edu>  Tue, 27 Nov 2007 14:49:08 -0500

openisr (0.8.4-1) experimental; urgency=low

   * New upstream release (see CHANGES):
      * use pv (dependency added)
      * openisr-config
      * 64 bit support
      * AES support
      * 'dirtometer' support
      * and more fixes
   * Debianized openisr-config (essentially a module-assistant wrapper)
   * postinst updated accordingly
   * eliminate openisr-modules-source package (and Conflict with it)
   * updated Build-Depends (linux-headers, amd64 libraries)

 -- Matt Toups <mtoups@cs.cmu.edu>  Tue, 20 Nov 2007 17:09:53 -0500

